<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-08-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="320" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-08-01"><hi rend="italic">August 1,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 93.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your No. 34, of the 22d ultimo,
                        you are instructed to request Lord Rosebery to permit the new British
                        consul-general at Sofia to continue the good offices heretofore so
                        courteously and efficiently extended in behalf of our citizens in Bulgaria
                        by Mr. Nicolas Roderick O’Oonor.</p>
                    <p>The Department has advised our minister at Constantinople of this
                        instruction.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>